<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="11" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,151,1183]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,333,268,294]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Mesosoma.</emphasis>
Pronotum with three lobes weakly defined (
<figureCitation box="[856,951,268,294]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="24.[151,257,1774,1798]" captionTargetBox="[178,1412,189,1773]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[151,1436,161,1853]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 13. Mesosoma in lateral view. a: Gasteruption bispinosum; b: G. guildingi; c: Plutofoenus chaeturus; d: P. edwardsi, e: P. paraguayensis; f: Spinolafoenus ruficornis; g: Trilobitofoenus alvarengai; h: T. plaumanni; i: T. sericeus. Scale bar: 1.0 mm. Lobes of pronotum: vl: ventral lobe; dl: dorsal lobe; ll: lateral lobe. Numbers indicate characters and respective synapomorphic states (within brackets)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/187231/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Figs. 
<number box="[923,951,268,294]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="13.0">13</number>
</figureCitation>
c-d); pronotal process present (
<figureCitation box="[1317,1412,268,294]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="24.[151,257,1774,1798]" captionTargetBox="[178,1412,189,1773]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[151,1436,161,1853]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 13. Mesosoma in lateral view. a: Gasteruption bispinosum; b: G. guildingi; c: Plutofoenus chaeturus; d: P. edwardsi, e: P. paraguayensis; f: Spinolafoenus ruficornis; g: Trilobitofoenus alvarengai; h: T. plaumanni; i: T. sericeus. Scale bar: 1.0 mm. Lobes of pronotum: vl: ventral lobe; dl: dorsal lobe; ll: lateral lobe. Numbers indicate characters and respective synapomorphic states (within brackets)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/187231/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Figs. 
<number box="[1384,1412,268,294]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="13.0">13</number>
</figureCitation>
c- e); propleuron simple anteriorly; mesonotum truncate in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[996,1094,306,332]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="24.[151,257,1774,1798]" captionTargetBox="[178,1412,189,1773]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[151,1436,161,1853]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 13. Mesosoma in lateral view. a: Gasteruption bispinosum; b: G. guildingi; c: Plutofoenus chaeturus; d: P. edwardsi, e: P. paraguayensis; f: Spinolafoenus ruficornis; g: Trilobitofoenus alvarengai; h: T. plaumanni; i: T. sericeus. Scale bar: 1.0 mm. Lobes of pronotum: vl: ventral lobe; dl: dorsal lobe; ll: lateral lobe. Numbers indicate characters and respective synapomorphic states (within brackets)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/187231/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Figs. 
<number box="[1065,1094,306,332]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="13.0">13</number>
</figureCitation>
c-e); mesoscutum uniformly sculptured, longer than wide, and almost forming a unique plane; with two lobes separated by depressed notauli (
<figureCitation box="[249,346,384,410]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="22.[151,255,1621,1645]" captionTargetBox="[176,1411,1011,1582]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[151,1436,993,1614]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 12. Mesonotum in dorsal view. a: Plutofoenus chaeturus; b: P. e d w a rd s i; c: P. paraguayensis; d: Spinolafoenus ruficornis; e: Trilobitofoenus alvarengai; f: T. plaumanni; g: T. sericeus. Scale bar: 1.0 mm. Numbers indicate characters and respective synapomorphic states (within brackets)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/187230/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Figs. 
<number box="[316,346,384,410]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="12.0">12</number>
</figureCitation>
a-c); parapsides distinct; mesepimeron entirely concave (
<figureCitation box="[1018,1114,384,410]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="24.[151,257,1774,1798]" captionTargetBox="[178,1412,189,1773]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[151,1436,161,1853]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 13. Mesosoma in lateral view. a: Gasteruption bispinosum; b: G. guildingi; c: Plutofoenus chaeturus; d: P. edwardsi, e: P. paraguayensis; f: Spinolafoenus ruficornis; g: Trilobitofoenus alvarengai; h: T. plaumanni; i: T. sericeus. Scale bar: 1.0 mm. Lobes of pronotum: vl: ventral lobe; dl: dorsal lobe; ll: lateral lobe. Numbers indicate characters and respective synapomorphic states (within brackets)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/187231/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Figs. 
<number box="[1085,1114,384,410]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="13.0">13</number>
</figureCitation>
c-e); fore and middle tibiae with a white stripe from base to apex; hind tibia white basally; metacoxa with fine transversal striae at posterior portion (
<figureCitation box="[369,458,461,487]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="25.[151,258,1435,1459]" captionTargetBox="[287,1310,438,1409]" captionTargetId="figure@25.[252,1334,429,1515]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURE 14. Propodeum and metacoxa in dorsal view. a: Gasteruption bispinosum; b – c: Plutofoenus edwardsi; d: Gasteruption sp. I; e: Spinolafoenus ruficornis; f: Trilobitofoenus plaumanni. Scale bar: 1.0 mm. Numbers indicate characters and respective synapomorphic states (within brackets)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/187232/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Fig. 
<number box="[426,458,461,487]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="14.0">14</number>
</figureCitation>
b); median propodeal carina convex and percurrent (
<figureCitation box="[1089,1187,461,487]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="25.[151,258,1435,1459]" captionTargetBox="[287,1310,438,1409]" captionTargetId="figure@25.[252,1334,429,1515]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURE 14. Propodeum and metacoxa in dorsal view. a: Gasteruption bispinosum; b – c: Plutofoenus edwardsi; d: Gasteruption sp. I; e: Spinolafoenus ruficornis; f: Trilobitofoenus plaumanni. Scale bar: 1.0 mm. Numbers indicate characters and respective synapomorphic states (within brackets)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/187232/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Figs. 
<number box="[1157,1187,461,487]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="14.0">14</number>
</figureCitation>
b-c); fore wing jugal lobe present; discal cell present, subtrapezoidal (
<figureCitation box="[724,796,500,526]" captionStart="FIGURE 7. a – b" captionStartId="17.[151,255,1753,1777]" captionTargetBox="[162,1423,182,1727]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[151,1436,164,1867]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 7. a – b: Left fore wing (scale bar: 1.0 mm). a: Pseudofoenus infumatus; b: Gasteruption bispinosum; c – h: Left fore wing discal cell (without scale); c: G. bispinosum; d: G. p a r v u m; e: Plutofoenus edwardsi; f: Spinolafoenus ruficornis; g: Trilobitofoenus plaumanni; h: T. alvarengai. Numbers indicate characters and respective synapomorphic" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/187225/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Fig. 
<number box="[780,796,500,526]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
e), vein r–m present, not reaching vein 
<number box="[1259,1274,500,526]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="2.0">2</number>
-m, vein 
<number box="[1380,1394,500,526]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="2.0">2</number>
–M tubular in first 
<number box="[329,340,538,564]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[352,367,538,564]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="3.0">3</number>
and nebulous in remaining portion (Fig. 
<number box="[857,872,538,564]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="3.0">3</number>
a); hind wing with 
<number box="[1100,1143,538,564]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="4.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="3.0">3–6</number>
equidistant hamuli (Fig. 
<number box="[151,166,577,603]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="3.0">3</number>
a).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,151,1183]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,332,615,641]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Metasoma.</emphasis>
First metasomal tergum with edges separate, not concealing first sternum (
<figureCitation box="[1241,1314,616,642]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="19.[151,256,1040,1064]" captionTargetBox="[505,1051,191,988]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[476,1112,180,1034]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 9. First metasomal segment in ventral view. a: Gasteruption bispinosum; b: Plutofoenus edwardsi. S 2: first metasomal sternum; T 2: first metasomal tergum. Without scale. Numbers indicate characters and respective synapomorphic states (within brackets)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/187227/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Fig. 
<number box="[1298,1314,616,642]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
b); female subgenital sternum with a slitlikeY-shaped notch (as 
<figureCitation box="[770,855,654,680]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="20.[151,255,853,877]" captionTargetBox="[229,1372,465,784]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[151,1436,419,846]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 10. Subgenital sternum in ventral view. a: notched, Y-shaped; b: notched, V-shaped; c: simple. Without scale. Numbers indicate characters and respective synapomorphic states (within brackets)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/187228/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Fig. 
<number box="[824,855,654,680]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
a); ovipositor longer than metasoma (Fig. 
<number box="[1347,1363,654,680]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="3.0">3</number>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="11" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,151,1183]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,350,693,719]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Distribution</emphasis>
. South 
<collectingCountry box="[441,547,693,719]" name="United States of America" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">America</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingCountry box="[559,679,693,719]" name="Argentina" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Argentina</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[690,800,693,719]" name="Paraguay" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
, southern 
<collectingCountry box="[921,993,693,719]" name="Brazil" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[1010,1097,693,719]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="26.[151,255,1356,1380]" captionTargetBox="[191,1401,198,1322]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[175,1411,179,1349]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 15. Geographic distribution of the species of Plutofoenus, Spinolafoenus and Trilobitofoenus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/187233/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Fig. 
<number box="[1065,1097,693,719]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="15.0">15</number>
</figureCitation>
). The species occur between 
<number box="[151,180,732,758]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="23.0">23</number>
ºS and 
<number box="[264,293,732,758]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="33.0">33</number>
ºS in subtropical areas, with substantial rainfall in the eastern portions, becoming semiarid in the western and southern portions. This distribution is very similar to the distribution of the only two species of Hyptiogastrinae in the Neotropical Region (
<bibRefCitation author="Jennings" box="[674,1003,809,835]" pageId="10" pageNumber="29" refString="Jennings, J. T. &amp; Austin, A. D. (1997 a) Revision of Aulacofoenus Kieffer (Hymenoptera: Gasteruptiidae), hyptiogastrine wasps with a restricted gondwanic distribution. Invertebrate Taxonomy, 11, 943 - 976." type="journal article" year="1997" yearSuffix="a">
Jennings and Austin 
<number box="[926,989,809,835]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="1997.0">1997</number>
a
</bibRefCitation>
). However, the species are very rare and additional collections are needed to confirm this pattern. At least one species seems to occur in the eastern Andean slopes (
<emphasis box="[340,471,887,912]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">P. e d w a rd s i</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[197,428,925,951]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,151,1183]" box="[197,428,925,951]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,297,925,951]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Biology.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="11" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,151,1183]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,339,963,989]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Comments.</emphasis>
This genus was defined by 
<bibRefCitation author="Kieffer" box="[665,834,964,990]" pageId="10" pageNumber="29" refString="Kieffer, J. J. (1911) Etude sur les evaniides exotiques (Hym.) du British Museum de Londres. Annales de la Societ Entomologique de France, 80, 151 - 231." type="journal article" year="1911">
Kieffer (
<number box="[765,825,964,990]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="1911.0">1911</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
to accommodate a single species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Schrottky" authorityName="Schrottky" class="Insecta" family="Gasteruptiidae" genus="Plutofoenus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paraguayensis">
<emphasis box="[1236,1436,964,989]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">P. paraguayensis</emphasis>
(Schrottky)
</taxonomicName>
, based only on the presence of the partially developed vein r-m, a character shown here to be plesiomorphic. 
<bibRefCitation author="Crosskey" box="[333,527,1041,1067]" pageId="10" pageNumber="28" refString="Crosskey, R. W. (1962) The classification of the Gasteruptiidae (Hymenoptera). Transactions of the Royal Entomological Society of London, 114, 377 - 402." type="journal article" year="1962">
Crosskey (
<number box="[458,519,1041,1067]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="1962.0">1962</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
synonymized 
<taxonomicName box="[699,839,1041,1066]" class="Insecta" family="Gasteruptiidae" genus="Plutofoenus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[699,839,1041,1066]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Plutofoenus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
under 
<emphasis box="[921,1083,1041,1066]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<taxonomicName box="[921,1079,1041,1066]" class="Insecta" family="Gasteruptiidae" genus="Gasteruption" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Gasteruption</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
However, 
<taxonomicName box="[1211,1351,1041,1066]" class="Insecta" family="Gasteruptiidae" genus="Plutofoenus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1211,1351,1041,1066]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Plutofoenus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is here revalidated because its species share nine synapomorphies (fully explained in the cladistic analysis section). 
<taxonomicName authority="Turner" authorityName="Turner" box="[151,493,1118,1144]" class="Insecta" family="Gasteruptiidae" genus="Plutofoenus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="edwardsi">
<emphasis box="[151,406,1119,1144]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Plutofoenus edwardsi</emphasis>
Turner
</taxonomicName>
was the only other described species in this genus (
<bibRefCitation author="Turner" box="[1108,1260,1118,1144]" pageId="10" pageNumber="30" refString="Turner, R. E. (1927) New Parasitic Hymenoptera in the British Museum. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, 9, 553 - 560." type="journal article" year="1927">
Turner 
<number box="[1197,1260,1118,1144]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="1927.0">1927</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authority="Schletterer" authorityName="Schletterer" class="Insecta" family="Gasteruptiidae" genus="Gasteruption" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chaeturum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Gasteruption chaeturum</emphasis>
Schletterer
</taxonomicName>
is here transferred to 
<emphasis box="[667,815,1157,1182]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<taxonomicName box="[667,811,1157,1182]" class="Insecta" family="Gasteruptiidae" genus="Plutofoenus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Plutofoenus</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
